          "fill": "$ink",
          "content": "Recommendation — compose all three, one per altitude",
          "fontFamily": "$font-head",
          "fontSize": 15,
          "fontWeight": "600"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "NIakm",
          "name": "RB",
          "fill": "$text-2",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "content": "These aren't competing skins — they're different altitudes of the same data. Proposed composition for /validate:\n\n• C (Tier Stack rows) = the DRC results list. Compact, scales, maps 1:1 to the engine's pipeline stages and diagnostic codes.\n• B (Breakout Funnel) = the spatial view inside an expanded row (or the slot-rail edge detail). It's the view that teaches interface ⊃ slot ⊃ leaf composition and makes inference visible as a ghost container.\n• A (Harness Table) = the export/'build it' view — printable WireViz-style wiring sheet with wire colors, one per harness.\n\nShared vocabulary board (left) is the contract all three obey: tier → line pattern + badge, state → color, inferred → purple + dashed + * + sparkle.",
          "fontFamily": "$font-body",
          "fontSize": 12,
          "fontWeight": "normal"
        }
      ]
    },
