              "fill": "$text-2",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Each composed interface is a soft-filled region; sub-interfaces are lighter regions inside it; leaves are chips. Depth = fill, not indentation. The harness lane mirrors the same tree: conductors are grouped into labeled bundles per sub-interface, so the wiring reads as the same shape as the composition. Example: a smart-actuator port (Dynamixel-style) — actuator_port ⊃ { uart ⊃ tx/rx, power_12v ⊃ v+/gnd }.",
