              "content": "Every interface on both modules is shown, PCB-symbol style: two columns per module, interior sides reserved for connectable interfaces, exterior sides carry the rest, both populated evenly. Port state carries the census: ● connected · ◉ compatible but unconnected · ○ no counterpart on the other module. Below: the match-altitude problem — when a child sub-interface matches on its own, the connection attaches at that child's port and the parent reports partial engagement.",
