            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "QabJM",
              "name": "Rules",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "fill": "$surface",
              "cornerRadius": 8,
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 4,
              "padding": [
                12,
                14
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "meNWv",
                  "name": "RT",
                  "fill": "$text-3",
                  "content": "MATCH-ALTITUDE RULES",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-mono",
                  "fontSize": 10,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "letterSpacing": 1
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "PU6j7",
                  "name": "R",
                  "fill": "$text-2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "1 · The engine pairs top-down and connects at the HIGHEST level both sides declare — one pill per match, attached to the port of the exact region that matched.",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "UcAK1",
                  "name": "R",
                  "fill": "$text-2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "2 · When only a child matches, the line exits through the parent's region edge; the parent port becomes a donut (partially engaged) and reports n of m subs.",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "g46Hzt",
                  "name": "R",
                  "fill": "$text-2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "3 · Deeper regions under a connected parent don't re-pair — the bundle view (B1) already shows their conductor crossings. Their ports render solid, inherited.",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "ECMfp",
                  "name": "R",
                  "fill": "$text-2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "4 · Remaining unengaged children keep live hollow ports — power_12v here can still pair with a third module via split fulfillment (B4).",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "xlNb1",
                  "name": "R",
                  "fill": "$text-2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "5 · Altitude asymmetry is fine: A connects at sub-interface level while B connects at its top level. The pill names both roles; tier/params evaluate on the matched pair only.",
                  "fontFamily": "$font-body",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
